&lt;b&gt;On what operating system?&lt;/b&gt;
windows
&lt;b&gt;What browser are you using?&lt;/b&gt;
chrome
&lt;b&gt;Please include version information for both the OS and the browser.&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;What steps will reproduce the problem?&lt;/b&gt;
1. play some audio inside nacl
2. crash the nacl process
3. try to play uadio 

&lt;b&gt;What is the expected output?&lt;/b&gt;
audio should play

&lt;b&gt;What do you see instead?&lt;/b&gt;
no audio plays



Please provide any additional information below and attach any relevant source files.
This was reported from FMOD:
&amp;quot;We've noticed that if the game crashes and the user reopens in a new
browser tab instead of closing and restarting chrome, there's no
audio.

It appears NaCl is leaking resources from the host chrome instance. Once the limit has been reached no audio can no longer be played in the browser, including HTML5 video&amp;quot;


